<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/53001534/2025-26/evaluation> a ns1:EvaluationSystem ;
    ns1:evaluationDescription """The evaluation is based on a final exam that covers the whole subject and a digital evaluation activity. The subject has two different contents, digital systems content and power electronics content, and the exam will have two parts as well.
To pass the subject it is mandatory to get at least 5 out of 10 in the total score of the exam, and at least a 35% of the maximum mark of each part. The digital systems score is composed of the final exam (70%) and the digital evaluation activity (30%). The later is carried out during the digital system classes.
FM is the Final Mark of the exam
PM is the Mark in the Power Electronics part
DM is the Mark in the Digital Systems part
FM = 0.5*PM + 0.5*DM if PM > 3.5 and DM > 3.5; else FM < 5
If January exam is failed but one of the parts is passed (PM>5 or DM>5), this mark will be kept for the July Exam and the student must only do the failed part in the July Exam."""@es ;
    ns1:hasEvaluationTrial <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/53001534/2025-26/evaluation/trial1>,
        <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/53001534/2025-26/evaluation/trial2>,
        <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/53001534/2025-26/evaluation/trial3> .

